article.headline: No. 12 Baylor hangs on as Kansas State rally falls short
article.linkText: Mosby's 29 points, 10 boards lead Baylor over K-State
article.story:
WACO, Texas (AP) -- Bernice Mosby scored 29 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Baylor (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today; No. 13 AP) to a 79-70 win over Kansas State (No. 25 AP) on Saturday.

Latara Darrett added 15 points for the Lady Bears (16-3, 3-2 Big 12), while Jessica Morrow had 14 and Angela Tisdale 12.

Shana Wheeler's jumper pulled the Wildcats (14-4, 2-3) to within two points at 72-70 with just under three minutes remaining.

But Kansas State never scored again, and Morrow's 3-pointer put the Lady Bears ahead 77-70 with a 1½ minutes left to play. Darrett's pair of free throws sealed the win with 33 seconds remaining.

Claire Coggins and Shalee Lehning led the Wildcats with 20 points each.

A 3-pointer by Kimberly Dietz put the Wildcats in front 37-35 with 3½ minutes left before halftime. But Baylor closed out the first half on a 10-1 run and took a 45-38 halftime lead.

Mosby's three-point play put the Lady Bears ahead 40-37 at 2:23, and Morrow's 3-pointer capped the outburst with 3 seconds left.

Mosby and Morrow paced Baylor's first-half scoring with 17 and 11 points, respectively, while Lehning led Kansas State with 14.
